com.ibm.team.scm.common

Interface IFolder

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IFolderHandle, IItem, IItemHandle, IUnmanagedItem, IUnmanagedItemHandle, IVersionable, IVersionableHandle

    public interface IFolder
extends IFolderHandle, IVersionable
    Represents a folder in the repository.

    Folders are the sole versionable container type. Each folder instance may contain a collection of other versionable items, including folders. These are called the folder's children. Each versionable item has a distinct name relative to its parent folder; however, these names are not intrinsic to the items; rather they are supplied by the parent folder. This means that changing the name of an item only requires changing the parent folder.

    Versionable items are arranged into trees. Within each configuration, each versionable item has a unique parent and a unique parent-relative name. The parent of an item is awlays a folder item, except for component root folders which have no parent. Note that Unix-style hard links are not supported, and folders are not allowed to directly or indirectly be their own parent (i.e., things must be cycle-free). We do not allow for subclasses of Folder at this time.

    Feature access profile values:

    • interestingToFileSystem: DEFAULT
    • entries: DEFAULT

    Since:
    0.5
